    en: "New York General Business Law Article 7 (Sections 70-89) requires licensing of private investigators, watchmen/guards, and bail enforcement agents. A licensed PI must have at least 3 years of full-time investigative experience, pass an exam, complete background check, and post a $10,000 surety bond. Unlicensed investigation for hire is a misdemeanor. Licensed PIs are subject to regulation by NYS Department of State and can lose their license for misconduct, privacy violations, or unlawful surveillance. Consumers hiring a PI should verify the license, demand a written contract, and understand that certain activities (wiretapping, GPS tracking without consent, misrepresenting to obtain info) are illegal regardless of the PI's license."
